<br>
We were a &quot;casual&quot; raiding guild meaning that attendance wasn't 100% required. But points were absolute and could not be disputed. So often times on raid nights, Player_01 could show 3 minutes prior to engaging Mob_01, skipping hours of mob clearing by the guild, be there for the kill and bid on items. It was funny watching everyone playing twinks midway through raids but then when it got closer to the target mob, mains start showing up.<br>
<br>
Also, points were permanent. So if someone leaves the guild and is then reinstated down the line, all raid points are returned to them. One long-time member in particular, gave up officer status and quit the guild to try out for a more uber guild. He was very explicit as to his reason for leaving us, he said our guild wasn't getting him the level of loot he wanted. Seriously. Anyway, he quits us, tries out, then gets rejected by the uber guild, so he &quot;retired&quot; for 2 months (during which time he asked a few people to take over his account, no one wanted it), then came crawling back with his tail between his legs, begs to rejoin and gets all his points back. He was high on points before he left (since he was an officer and all) so as soon as he comes back starts looting. I have no doubt that this guy is simply trying to increase his value so if/when he attempts to join some other guild, he'll have a better shot.<br>
<br>
But, like I said, that's my ex-guild so I'm not bitter or anything. The fact that that guy and I were the same class and I kept getting outbid on loot is merely a coincidence. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=chidder>Chidder</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/6/03 8:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1958.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: .loot assingment</span><hr size=1> that really sucks about that officer. See  in our guild if you leave the guild your points go poof. Also if u stop playing with out being retired your points will also start poofin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zambukkabeast>Zambukkabeast</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/7/03 2:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1958.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: .loot assingment</span><hr size=1> We use officers to decide.  And I have yet to see one item assigned poorly.  Even in the best of times one would expect a screw up or a misplaced loot, but they do a damn fine job.<br>
