Loot price is determined by a excel spreadsheet that calculates it from a base item and the top item attainable by the guild at the time.<br>
<br>
Overall I think it's a very fair system and as other people mentioned, it's pretty much the most unbiased system (you put your work on the guild  you get more points than casual members &gt; more loot) although it has it's disadvantages too <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=11869&amp;resize=true">Breogan Wolfheart</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> - <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.tunare-europa.co.uk/tide">Overlord of Tide</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=khursed>Khur Sed</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 65<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/11/03 7:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1958.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: .loot assingment</span><hr size=1> we have a complicated system that works fairly well.<br>
<br>
The officer sold all our guilds pp on ebay for phat money, and bought a steel cage, and 55 monkees, since we have 55 members.<br>
<br>
whenever someone wants a loot, he takes a black marker, and does an x on the balls of a pre-numbered monkee, that will then be put into the steel cage.<br>
<br>
Since the monkee are very infrequently fed, and are all males, also all blind. He just shakes the cage a lot, and then pulls one out randomly, after they've fought for a while, its usually the winner who is picked up.<br>
<br>
So if he picked your monkee, you win the loot. He then sprays female hormones on the winners monkee, and then throws it back in the cage for 10 minutes. So next time phat loot drops, your monkee won't be in any shape to be picked.<br>
<br>
This method as several advantage. 1, your monkee can only endure so much pain so if you win, you will have to wait until your monkee recovers enuff to roll again, 2 if your monkee dies, you aren't worthy to be with us, and we deguild you on the spot, because that means you've abuse the poor creature by trying to roll too soon on phat loot. <p>Overlord of the brell server<br>
